children.text: The roof tiles in this area are not overhanging the fascia at least 35mm to ensure that roof water collected is discharged into the gutter.
Part 3.5.2.6 Water discharge of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia (BCA), requires that
‘tiles must overhang the fascia or tiling batten by not less than 35mm (See Figure 3.5.2.4)’ ;
The builder must ensure that the roof tiles overhang into the gutter in accordance with this requirement of the Building Code of Australia (BCA).
